<br>
So when EQ2 comes out, does everyone think EQ will 'die'?<br>
<br>
Again, I have no idea really.  Whatcha all think? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1508<br> <font color=#333333>(12/11/02 6:19:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8123.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where is EQ going to go?</span><hr size=1> Well the official word is &quot;we will continute to support EQ as long as people are playing it&quot;.  However, my opinion is the game is getting pretty close to maximum potential.  It is already so incredibly HUGE that many people will never explore all the zones available.<br>
<br>
Will a lot of people leave to go play EQ2?  That remains to be seen.  Will they make yet another expansion?  Probably not until after the EQ2 release is done, and by then they will have a better idea of how much customer base is left in EQ.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=archangelranari@themagicianstower>Archangel Ranari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(12/11/02 7:01:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8123.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where is EQ going to go?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> It is already so incredibly HUGE that many people will never explore all the zones available. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Huge?  Yes.  Utilized properly.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> No. </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
There are many zones which could use a good revamp.  Having all the classes in Paludal Caverns from level 5 to 27 (which you can very easily do) in 2-3 RL days, in my opinion, is not balancing. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
In case anyone hasn't noticed, Verant is putting all the best of everything, better than the previous content, in their latest expansions just so we'll buy it.  Don't get me wrong, I don't have any problem with VI making money, but they're meant to be expansions that add content, not expansions that negate all the previous expansions before it.  When I say that though, I'm mainly speaking for the lower levels (1-50).<br>
<br>
PoP isn't included in that semi-rantish response, as PoP is aimed for the 60+ crowd (so it seems...).  However, PoP brings about an entire slew of so called &quot;problems&quot; that have been discussed many times amongst the boards of all classes.  I won't get into that, nor do I feel I have the knowledge to defend it even if I did!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I must say one thing though, PoP trivializing a lot of the older content, however it does allow for much MORE content to be added.  Expansions are based off of player levels, which spells, resists, attack, defense, are all based around also.  Verant could easily add 2-3 more expansions, maybe even another playable race or two, utilizing the level 65 maximum.  <br>
<br>
On a side note, I would LOVE to see Frogloks and Sarnaks added as playable races.  <br>
